    <subfield code="a">In this letter, Louisa Phillips writes: &quot;On Wednesday next the constitution for our society will be drawn up---next week the Rev. Mr. May (what a good man he is!) will deliver an address---[and] our Society will be formed.&quot; The Liberator is appreciated. Louisa Phillips suggests, however, that one of the copies be directed to her friend Miss Elizabeth Lewis, from whom she has learned that there is a need for anti-slavery literature in North Duxbury. Miss Lewis is a recent convert. Louisa Phillips requests that Maria Weston Chapman select books for Phillips&apos; anti-slavery society.</subfield>
